{
  "text": "Xiao and Boyd [CITATION_1] also identify a suboptimal approach that leads to a much less demanding algorithm. In this approach, neighboring edge weights are set to a constant, and the constant is optimized. The optimal constant is inversely proportional to the sum of the largest and the second smallest eigenvalues of the Laplacian spectrum. The calculation thus still requires knowledge of the connectivity pattern. The resultant weight matrix is called the \"best constant\" weight matrix in [CITATION_2] . The suboptimality of the best constant weight matrix stems from the fact that all the edge weights are constrained to be the same.",
